{"lemma":"سَقِيم","slug":"سَقِيم","root":"س.ق.م","root_slug":"س-ق-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ق-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَقِيم","root":"سقم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20128"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"weak"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sick, ailing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"faulty","examples":[{"text":"a. 966, Al-Mutanabbi\nوَكَمْ مِنْ عَائِبٍ قَوْلًا صَحِيحًا / وَآفَتُهُ مِنَ الْفَهْمِ السَّقِيمِ\nwakam min ʕāʔibin qawlan ṣaḥīḥan / waʔāfatuhū mina l-fahmi as-saqīmi\nAnd how many are those who criticize a sound saying – while the fault is in their ill understanding!"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb سَقُمَ (saquma, “to become ill”)."},"ipa":["/sa.qiːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20128","headword_ar":"سَقِيمٌ","root":"sqm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diseased, disordered, distempered, sick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqimN","text_ar":"سَقِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long diseased"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (Msb:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaAmN","text_ar":"سِقَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiraAmN","text_ar":"كِرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kariymN","text_ar":"كَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoqaAmN","text_ar":"مِسْقَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musoqimN","text_ar":"مُسْقِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iniy saqiymN","text_ar":"اـِنِي سَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in the Kur [xxxvii. 87], as a saying of Abraham, is expl. by some as meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I am"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smitten with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAEuwn","text_ar":"طَاعُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pestilence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I shall be diseased"},{"kind":"text","text":"at a future time, when the period shall have come; and it is said that he inferred, from looking at the stars, the time of a fever's coming to him: or it means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verily I am sick of your worshipping what is not God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"IAth says that, in truth, it is one of his three lies; all of which were for the sake of God and his religion. (TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobN saqiymN","text_ar":"قَلْبٌ سَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A diseased, a sickly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsound, heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahomN saqiymN","text_ar":"فَهْمٌ سَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diseased, unsound, faulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak, understanding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAmN saqiymN","text_ar":"كَلَامٌ سَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unsound, faulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak, language"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa saqiymu AlS~adori Ealayohi","text_ar":"هُوَ سَقِيمُ الصَّدْرِ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is affected with rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite, against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","K"]}]}}